# Git Commit → Push → Release Deploy (Consolidated One-Shot)

Use this rule when the user asks to **commit and push** named project(s), **include unstaged/untracked files** (after secret filtering), **sync cursor git rules**, and **merge into release/deploy branches** for production builds.

**Detail rules (read when needed):**
- [git_local_push.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_local_push.mdc) — secret blocklist, SSL workaround, unstaged/untracked staging
- [git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc) — batch workflow for mosc-temp + batch-jobs + service
- [deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc) — **push release/deploy branches**, GH_TOKEN auth, Amplify/ECS verify, SQL file-lock ref-push workaround

---

## **Copy-paste user prompt (one shot)**

```
Commit and push these projects:
- F:\project_workspace\<repo-1>
- F:\project_workspace\<repo-2>

Include all unstaged and untracked files if they pass the secret filter (no .env, keys, auth.json, credentials).
Sync .cursor/rules/git_local_push.mdc and git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc from common_project_work.
Then merge each repo into its release/deploy branch and push for production deployments.

Follow git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc.
```

