## **Agent checklist (every request)**

### **Phase 0a — GitHub auth (before any push)**

Load User-level `GH_TOKEN` on this machine — **required** for agent/automated pushes (stale keychain `gh` login will fail):

```powershell
$env:GH_TOKEN = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable('GH_TOKEN', 'User')
gh auth setup-git
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'
gh auth status   # expect: Logged in to github.com … (GH_TOKEN)
```

See [deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc) Phase 0. Do **not** run `gh auth login` interactively when `GH_TOKEN` is valid.

### **Phase 0 — Pull remote FIRST (before commit or release merge)**

See [git_local_push.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_local_push.mdc) **Phase 0**. For each repo:

```powershell
git fetch origin
git pull origin <work-branch>
git diff --name-only --diff-filter=U   # must be empty before commit
```

- Resolve conflicts locally; if unresolvable → **BLOCKER** (report and skip that repo).
- Repos with no blockers continue through Phases 1–6.

### **Phase 1 — Inspect (parallel per repo)**

```powershell
cd F:\project_workspace\<repo>
git status -sb
git status --porcelain
git branch --show-current
git diff --stat
```

### **Phase 2 — Sync cursor git rules (from canonical source)**

Canonical copies live in `F:\project_workspace\common_project_work\.cursor\rules\`:

```powershell
$canonical = 'F:\project_workspace\common_project_work\.cursor\rules'
$dest = 'F:\project_workspace\<repo>\.cursor\rules'
Copy-Item "$canonical\git_local_push.mdc" "$dest\git_local_push.mdc" -Force
Copy-Item "$canonical\git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc" "$dest\git_commit_push_core_repos.mdc" -Force
Copy-Item "$canonical\git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc" "$dest\git_commit_push_release_deploy.mdc" -Force
Copy-Item "$canonical\deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc" "$dest\deploy_apps_to_amplify_ecs.mdc" -Force
```

Also commit rule updates back to **common_project_work** and **application-deployments** when this consolidated rule changes.

### **Phase 3 — Stage ALL safe changes (unstaged + untracked)**

When `git status --porcelain` is non-empty:

```powershell
git add -A
git restore --staged tsconfig.tsbuildinfo 2>$null
git restore --staged code_html_template/SQLS/corrected_event_media_inserts.ordered_PROD.sql 2>$null
git diff --cached --name-only | Select-String -Pattern `
  'prod\.env$|\.env\.local|\.env\.production|auth\.json$|\.auth-state|secrets|\.pem$|\.key$|credentials|ordered_PROD\.sql|tsconfig\.tsbuildinfo$' `
  -CaseSensitive:$false | ForEach-Object { git restore --staged $_.Line.Trim() }
```

**Secret scan (required — empty output before commit):**

```powershell
git diff --cached --name-only | Select-String -Pattern `
  'prod\.env$|\.env\.local|\.env\.production|auth\.json|\.auth-state|secrets|\.pem$|\.key$|credentials' `
  -CaseSensitive:$false
```

- **DO** commit app code, docs, SQL artifacts, and `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` together when safe.
- **DON'T** commit only rules while other unstaged app files remain — unless user scoped to rules only.

If nothing to commit after scan, skip to Phase 5 (release merge may still be needed).

### **Phase 4 — Commit and push work branch**

```powershell
git commit -m "<type(scope): message from diff>"
$env:GH_TOKEN = [Environment]::GetEnvironmentVariable('GH_TOKEN', 'User')
gh auth setup-git
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'
git push origin <current-branch>
Remove-Item Env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY
git status --porcelain
```

Repeat until working tree is clean (except gitignored/blocklisted paths).

### **Phase 5 — Merge to deploy branch: pull, merge, resolve conflicts, push or PR**

**Always `git pull` on release before merge.** Resolve conflicts before push.

**Fast-forward (preferred)** when deploy branch has no unique prod commits:

```powershell
git fetch origin
git checkout release/v1.0.0
git pull origin release/v1.0.0
git reset --hard <work-branch>
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'
git push origin release/v1.0.0
Remove-Item Env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY
git checkout <work-branch>
```

**Merge (when release has prod-only commits ahead):**

```powershell
git checkout release/v1.0.0
git pull origin release/v1.0.0
git merge <work-branch> -m "merge: <work-branch> into release/v1.0.0 for deployment"
# On conflict: resolve, git add, git commit; or git merge --abort and report BLOCKER
$env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY = 'true'
git push origin release/v1.0.0
Remove-Item Env:GIT_SSL_NO_VERIFY
```

**If push rejected (protected branch):** `gh pr create --base release/v1.0.0 --head <work-branch>` → check mergeability → `gh pr merge` or report BLOCKER with PR URL and conflicted files.

**Repos with deploy branch = `main`:** push `main` only (no release step).

### **Phase 6 — Verify and report**

```powershell
git fetch origin
git rev-parse --short origin/<work-branch>
git rev-parse --short origin/<deploy-branch>   # should include work-branch changes
git status -sb
git status --porcelain
```

Report **COMPLETED** and **BLOCKERS** tables (see [git_local_push.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/git_local_push.mdc)). Continue commit/push for repos with no blockers.

